le=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 28, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fyg1665702910492.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fyg1665702910492.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fyg1665702910492.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fyg1665702910492\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Symbol Tables\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Symbol tables contain object references for compiled components, application shells, global ProcScript, menus, and panels. This information can be used to generate cross-reference data during compilation.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyg1665702910492__p_d43070e1_d43071e1_d43072e1\">Symbol tables are always available during compilation, so they can be used to generate cross-reference data directly in the UXCROSS data, or they can be written to files in the working directory, and later imported into the UXCROSS table. Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$SYMBOL_TABLE</span> assignment setting or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/sym</span> command line switch to determine this behavior. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mpw1665702656511.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mpw1665702656511.html\" title=\"Specifies whether symbol table files and cross-reference data are generated during compilation.\">$SYMBOL_TABLE</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aqo1665702655995.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqo1665702655995.html\" title=\"Specify whether object references are generated during compilation, and where they are located.\">/sym</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyg1665702910492__p_d43073e1_d43074e1_d43075e1\">Symbol table files are written to the Uniface working directory (by default, <span class=\"ph filepath\">/project</span>) and use the naming conventions used for application resources , with the addition of <code class=\"ph codeph\">SYM</code> in the extension. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">APPLICATION.APSSYM\nCOMPONENT.CPTSYM\nCENTRALPROC@LIBRARY.CPRSYM\nMENU@LIBRARY@LANGUAGE.MENSYM\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyg1665702910492__p_d43076e1_d43077e1_d43078e1\">Each symbol table contains an associative list of objects referenced by components and ProcScript. The objects include models, entities, fields, components, ProcScript modules, global objects, files, and parameters. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"clx1665702910566.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/clx1665702910566.html\" title=\"Each symbol table contains an associative list of objects referenced by components and ProcScript. The objects include models, entities, fields, components, ProcScript modules, global objects, files, and parameters.\">Objects Included in Symbol Tables</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyg1665702910492__p_d43079e1_d43080e1_d43081e1\">Each object reference in a symbol table provides information about the object itself and where it is referenced, including the line number and source (trigger, include ProcScript, or local ProcScript), field, entity, model, and component. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gdj1665702910639.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gdj1665702910639.html\" title=\"Each object reference in a symbol table provides information about the object itself and where it is referenced, including the line number and source (trigger, IncludeScript, or local ProcScript), field, entity, model, and component.\">Object References in Symbol Tables</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mpw1665702656511.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$SYMBOL_TABLE</a><p>Specifies whether symbol table files and cross-reference data are generated during compilation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqo1665702655995.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/sym</a><p>Specify whether object references are generated during compilation, and where they are located.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nvg1665702737302.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>UXCROSS</a><p>UXCROSS is a repository table that is used to create cross-reference reports. It is populated with information in symbol tables.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvd1665702658647.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Standardized Directory Structure</a><p>Runtime objects are always stored in a fixed directory structure, whether that is in a compilation output directory or a deployed Uniface archive file.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pzb1665702910715.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Generate and Maintain Cross-Reference Data</a><p>Cross-reference data is maintained in the UXCROSS repository table. Once the UXCROSS table exists, you can use the Cross Reference utility to import information from symbol table files in the working directory or delete cross-reference records from the table.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527738\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527738\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Symbol Tables Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 28, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Symbol Tables Symbol tables contain object references for compiled components, application shells, global ProcScript, menus, and panels. This information can be used to generate cross-reference data during compilation. Symbol tables are always available during compilation, so they can be used to generate cross-reference data directly in the UXCROSS data, or they can be written to files in the working directory, and later imported into the UXCROSS table. Use the $SYMBOL_TABLE assignment setting or /sym command line switch to determine this behavior. For more information, see $SYMBOL_TABLE and /sym . Symbol table files are written to the Uniface working directory (by default, /project ) and use the naming conventions used for application resources , with the addition of SYM in the extension. For example: APPLICATION.APSSYM COMPONENT.CPTSYM CENTRALPROC@LIBRARY.CPRSYM MENU@LIBRARY@LANGUAGE.MENSYM Copy Each symbol table contains an associative list of objects referenced by components and ProcScript. The objects include models, entities, fields, components, ProcScript modules, global objects, files, and parameters. For more information, see Objects Included in Symbol Tables . Each object reference in a symbol table provides information about the object itself and where it is referenced, including the line number and source (trigger, include ProcScript, or local ProcScript), field, entity, model, and component. For more information, see Object References in Symbol Tables . Related Links $SYMBOL_TABLE Specifies whether symbol table files and cross-reference data are generated during compilation. /sym Specify whether object references are generated during compilation, and where they are located. UXCROSS UXCROSS is a repository table that is used to create cross-reference reports. It is populated with information in symbol tables. Standardized Directory Structure Runtime objects are always stored in a fixed directory structure, whether that is in a compilation output directory or a deployed Uniface archive file. Generate and Maintain Cross-Reference Data Cross-reference data is maintained in the UXCROSS repository table. Once the UXCROSS table exists, you can use the Cross Reference utility to import information from symbol table files in the working directory or delete cross-reference records from the table. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}